title: Elysian Fields - Bleed Your Cedar + Queen of the Meadow [FLAC]
description:
Elysian Fields got kickstarted in 1995 in the NYC indie music scene, spearheaded by the whispering, seductive vocals of Jennifer Charles.

Elysian Fields has found underground success in the United States but is more popular in Europe.

The band uses mainly acoustic instruments, predominantly guitar, piano, bass and drums, with the occasional appearance of eastern instruments, classical strings and subtle electronics.

Here (from 1996) is their first full-length album, Bleed Your Cedar, and (from 2000) their sophomore album Queen of the Meadow.
